> [!WARNING]
> **Windows Limitation Notice:** When performing the test execution on your machine, the `pip install` sequence specifically failed on downloading `PyTorch` (a dependency for Sentence-Transformers) because your Windows Operating System does not have **"Long Path Support"** enabled, preventing deep C++ file extraction (`ATen/native/transformers/cuda/mem_eff_attention/iterators/predicated_tile_access_iterator_residual_last.h`).

**To run the code successfully on your end, you must enable Long Paths in Windows.**
1. Press `Win + R`, type `regedit` and hit enter.
2. Navigate to `HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\FileSystem`.
3. Double-click `LongPathsEnabled` and set its value to `1`.
4. Close your terminal, restart it, and run `pip install -r chunking_embedding_service\requirements.txt`.
